## Pre-Retrain Checklist

Before approving this job, verify:

- [ ] Triggering signals reviewed and confirmed (not a pipeline defect)
- [ ] Training data pipeline is healthy (check data quality score)
- [ ] Sufficient new labelled data is available
  - Minimum recommended: {{ min_new_samples | default('10,000 samples') }}
- [ ] Compute budget approved for training run
- [ ] Eval suite is up-to-date and covers the drift-affected categories
- [ ] On-call ML engineer has been notified

---

## Retrain Steps

### 1. Trigger training run

```bash
# MLflow
mlflow run . -P model_name={{ model_name }} \
  --experiment-name {{ model_name }}-retrain \
  --tags triggering_job_id={{ job_id }}

# OR — SageMaker
aws sagemaker create-training-job \
  --training-job-name {{ model_name }}-retrain-{{ job_id[:8] }} \
  --tags Key=triggering_job_id,Value={{ job_id }}
```

### 2. Monitor training

The shadow-deployment-orchestrator will automatically:
- Register the new model version as `stage=shadow`
- Configure {{ shadow_traffic_pct }}% traffic split to the shadow model
- Monitor shadow eval pass rate against champion

### 3. Shadow evaluation period

Minimum shadow duration: **{{ min_shadow_hours | default(24) }} hours**

The orchestrator will notify you when:
- Shadow pass rate is within 2 pp of champion → promotion recommended
- Shadow pass rate falls > 5 pp below champion → shadow aborted

### 4. Promotion (requires human approval)

Once promotion criteria are met, the orchestrator will post a promotion
recommendation. You must approve in the admin UI or via IM reply.

```
# Admin UI
{{ admin_url }}/ml-ops/retrain/{{ job_id }}
```

---

## Rollback Plan

If the shadow model performs worse:

1. Reject the promotion recommendation in admin UI
2. The orchestrator will retire the candidate and restore full traffic to champion
3. File a Jira ticket with tag `ml-debt` to track root cause
4. Review eval category breakdown to identify failure mode

---

## Post-Retrain Verification

After promotion, verify:

- [ ] Champion stage updated in `mlops_model_versions`
- [ ] Prior champion stage = `retired`
- [ ] Regression eval pass rate >= pre-retrain baseline
- [ ] Drift signals resolved (no new signals within 48h)
- [ ] MLflow/SageMaker run tagged with `promoted=true`
- [ ] Jira ticket closed (if one was opened)

